title: David Bell Scores Two TDs in 4th Quarter as Browns Rest Starters Ahead of Playoff Matchup with Texans
text:
David Bell grabs 2 TDs in 4th quarter for late offensive spark in Browns loss to Bengals
David Bell grabs 2 TDs in 4th quarter for late offensive spark in Browns loss to Bengals
Heading into Week 18, the Browns had already secured a playoff spot and decided to rest their starters, giving a chance for their backups and younger players to gain valuable game experience. Despite the loss, this game does not affect their postseason.
Struggles for the Young Players and Backups
With the younger players and backups getting a chance to play, the Browns struggled both offensively and defensively. The defense gave up 31 points, and the offense couldnâ€™t find a rhythm in the passing or running game.
Looking Ahead to the Playoffs
Despite the loss, the Browns are not worried as they prepare for their playoff matchup. Their starters will be back on the field, and they will face the Texans in the Wild Card round of the playoffs.
The Browns will officially face the AFC South-winning Texans in the Wild Card round of the playoffs.
